    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-09T10:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-09T10:35:00-05:00" n="523"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363/12–944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-09T19:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 9, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 18—11:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>918. Court Minister Ala told me today Soviet Ambassador Maximov and Kavtaradze
                    had called on Prime Minister Bayat 2 or 3 days ago and Maximov had read
                    statement to effect that Soviet Government considered passage of law forbidding
                    oil negotiations as objectionable and obstructive and felt that it should be
                    revised.</p>
                <pb facs="0496" n="484" xml:id="pg_484"/>
                <p>Bayat replied that even if he wished he could do nothing about it since it was a
                    law enacted by the legislature.</p>
                <p>Kavtaradze left by air for Moscow this morning.</p>
                <p>To Department as No. 918; repeated Moscow as 112; repeated London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
